<div id="review_2194665310" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2194665310" />
    <a title="Hap182" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/74216823-hap182"><img alt="Hap182" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2194665310?book_show_action=true">Nov 25, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hap182" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hap182" href="/user/show/74216823-hap182">Hap182</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/12086697-small-as-a-mustard-seed">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2194665310" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2581996278332907473">A gripping story that captured my heart from the opening scene and stayed on my mind for days after I finished it.<br/> <br/>Small As A Mustard Seed was one of the few books where I felt compelled to ignore everything else around me so I could read through the book until the end. This was probably because Johnson lures her readers in with a beautiful voice that wraps itself around your heart and pulls you in deeper and deeper until you’re so engrossed you can’t help but read on to know what happens next f</span>
  <span id="freeText2581996278332907473" style="display:none">A gripping story that captured my heart from the opening scene and stayed on my mind for days after I finished it.<br /> <br />Small As A Mustard Seed was one of the few books where I felt compelled to ignore everything else around me so I could read through the book until the end. This was probably because Johnson lures her readers in with a beautiful voice that wraps itself around your heart and pulls you in deeper and deeper until you’re so engrossed you can’t help but read on to know what happens next for Jolene and Anne Marie. I felt like I was in the room with them, experiencing all of it. I felt that despite the seriousness of the father’s condition, a resilient spirit was present in Anne Marie’s character and I admired and loved that about her. How this author managed to find grace in the darkness is beyond me, but she does so in a beautiful and powerful way. This story will stay with you long after you’ve finished reading it. <br />I highly recommend this book. 5 Stars. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2581996278332907473" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


