<div id="review_357915170" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/357915170" />
    <a title="Ginny Lakes" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10526533-ginny-lakes"><img alt="Ginny Lakes" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/357915170?book_show_action=true">Jun 29, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ginny Lakes" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ginny Lakes" href="/user/show/10526533-ginny-lakes">Ginny Lakes</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/12086697-small-as-a-mustard-seed">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer357915170&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer357915170" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14752794875561961493">I liked this book well enough, but there were some things in it that were a little hard to swallow. I thought the characters were very well developed, but what threw me was that the sister whose point of view the story was told from was, to me, the least interesting character in the story. When the other sister died my interest in what happened to the others kind of fell off, which surprised me. But it was well written, if choppy at times.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


